By running a Bayesian regression on their model, I was able to find that their test was more robust than they may have expected. Not only did the coefficients match up from the lm() and stan_glm() models, the median absolute deviation also matches with the clusters of standard deviation found earlier. I was unable to run the cluster function on the Bayesian models and am planning to explore this futher.
